1. Multiple Classes

HTML :
<button class="btn primary login">

CSS :
.btn.primary.login

Playwright
e.g. -> await page.locator(".btn.primary.login").click();

2. Partial Attribute Match

Starts With
input[id^='user']

Ends With
input[id$='name']

Contains
input[id*='user']

Playwright
e.g. -> await page.locator("input[id*='user']").fill("Admin");

3. Multiple Attribute Matching

input[type='text'][name='username']

4. Parent → Child
CSS ->
form input

5. Direct Child
CSS ->
form > input

6. Adjacent Sibling
label + input

7. General Sibling
label ~ input

8. nth-child()
tbody tr:nth-child(4)

9. nth-of-type()
div:nth-of-type(2)

10. not()
input:not([disabled])

11. input:checked
input:checked

12. Empty Element
div:empty

13. Enabled
button:enabled

14. Disabled
button:disabled

15. Focus
input:focus


